This has become one of our favorite pork chop recipes. Some changes: I use goat cheese instead of roquefort. I buy two extra thick chops but make the same amount of stuffing. After stuffing and browning the chops, I spread the extra stuffing around them in the pan, and then bake in the oven as directed. For the bread cubes, I use pain de mie, a little twist on French bread that they sell at Standard Baking here in Portland. Finally, I do the baking step on the grill, not the oven, which gives an added little smoky taste. These are great..there is never even a crumb leftover.

